38Watts’s  response, delivered before a live audience in the Library of Congress, was  quickly overshadowed by the announcement of a verdict in the civil trial of  former NFL player O.J. Simpson. Some major networks divided their screen  between Simpson and Watts, quickly returning full coverage to Simpson’s trial  in California  at the end of the Representative’s statement. Katharine Q. Seelye, “G.O.P.,  After Fumbling in ’96, Turns to Orator for Response,” 5 February 1997, New  York Times: A1.
